<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>FAQ Section</title>

    <script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.6.0.min.js"></script>

    <style>
        body { font-family: Arial; padding: 20px; }
        .answer { display: none; margin-left: 20px; }
        .highlight { color: blue; font-weight: bold; }
        .question { cursor: pointer; margin-top: 10px; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

<div class="faq">
    <p class="question">1. What is jQuery?</p>
    <p class="answer">jQuery is a JavaScript library.</p>

    <p class="question">2. Why use jQuery?</p>
    <p class="answer">It simplifies DOM manipulation.</p>

    <p class="question">3. What is slideToggle?</p>
    <p class="answer">It shows and hides content smoothly.</p>

    <p class="question">4. Is jQuery still used?</p>
    <p class="answer">Yes, in many legacy systems.</p>

    <p class="question">5. How to include jQuery?</p>
    <p class="answer">Using CDN link in script tag.</p>
</div>

<script>
$(document).ready(function(){

    $(".question").click(function(){
         $(".answer").hide();
        $(this).next(".answer").slideToggle();
        $(this).toggleClass("highlight");
       
    });

});
</script>

</body>
</html>
